Andira (Granblue Fantasy)

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

This is a lycors\locon you have to use the additional networks extension or the lycoris extension for this to work.

Technically this model already exists if you want to scour the depth of 4-chan you might find it or maybe someone uploaded it somewhere.

I made this model to make it more available to the masses and also to decrease the size drastically.

Keyword is Andira works on strength 1.0 fine you can adjust it but that wont really increase the accuracy.

The character has a really complex outfit for the AI to grasp even if it doesn't look like it because she is barely wearing anything. The one thing that does mess up a lot are here ear decorations and her tail they sometimes merge or are not there at all I tried to retrain it with different tags and pruned different things but it didn't work out it is still not 100% consistent. Most of my preview images were generated on cfg scale 5 though maybe using a higher cfg scale fixes it.

But apart from that you can get everything pretty much all the time her hair might mess up sometimes but shouldn't be often but I highly recommend using short hair or you might get a long hair version of her because I didn't want to prune short hair because that would also mess up her hairstyle or at least make it not as consistent.

If you want to change the artstyle a bit you can use tags like "granblue fantasy" which worked as some kind of a style prompt for me even though this version doesn't have the tag anymore.

Everything considered I'm quite happy with it and I hope you are as well.

As always if you like it consider pressing the heart button if you want to share some of your generations with the community or have some questions feel free to leave a comment and if you want to do me a real solid one consider rating it as you see fit.

Have fun generating.

ギャラリーのように

Like Gallery,

[pocketbike: (motocompo:1.1) <lyco:motocompo_v10:0.5> :0.7]

If you use the prompt editing function, it is more likely to be generated with the correct modeling.

Still, the probability is not high, so please use it patiently.
